     Two further challenges rise from the observations of this session.  How shall we think
about the negotiating and cheating ?  How should we represent the opponent-specific	
knowledge that is so salient in play against her brother ?  Since the attempt to
negotiate alternate winning and the cheating of game 2.4 are both violations of
